    std::string markdownText = "# Heading 1\n"
                               "## Heading 2\n"
                               "Some **bold** text and some *italic* text.\n"
                               "Here is a link: [Google](https://www.google.com).";

    std::string htmlText = markdownToHtml(markdownText);

    std::cout << htmlText << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

Please note that this function uses regular expressions to perform simple replacements and is not a complete Markdown to HTML converter. Full Markdown parsing is a complex task due to the extensive syntax rules and edge cases, and typically requires a fully-featured library.

